div.p:
               Mr Feilder of Andover witneſſed,

That upon the Wedneſday and Thurſday of the Week, in which the Earl of Eſſex dyed, it was the common talk of the Town of Andover;

                  Note, in like manner it was proved in the Tayal of the Lord Stafford, that it was reported at a great diſtance, that Sr Edmundbury Godfrey had murdered himſelf before it was known at London what was become of him. that he had cut his Throat; that the Women talked of it, as they came in & out of the Town; and that on the Saturday night in that Week, the certain news of it came.

Jeffryes then addreſſed himſelf to the Lords, to this effect;
   Note, my Lord Delamere was at that time in the Houſe of Commons, and a great Promoter of the Bill of Excluſion. 
That their Lordſhips could not but remember the inſolent Attempts made upon the unalterable Succeſſion to the Crown, under the ſpetious pretence of Religion, by the fierce, froward and Fanatical Zeal of ſome of the Commons, which had been often found the occaſion of Rebellion.
